accessibility.text: Go back to where you woke up
You stand up，shakily like a new-born deer, and walk towards the flock, concentrating on your foot and trying not to fall down.

When getting closer, you finally realize that they are not \"common\" animals at all. They look like a flock of giant iron jellyfish, with multiple blinking yellow \"eyes\" on each of their soft legs. They are strangely floating over the grass, turning their heads around, and communicating with each other with some kind of vibration.
\"I'd better not get too close. It's obvious that I cannot talk to them in my language or by vibrating my head.\" You talk to yourself ironically.
